SIMPLE: plastron
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plastron
<hw>Plas"tron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>plastron</ets> breastplate, plastron, LL. <ets>plastra</ets> a thin
plate of metal. See <er>Plaster</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A piece of
leather stuffed or padded, worn by fencers to protect the breast.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anc. Armor)</fld> <def>An iron breastplate, worn
under the hauberk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The ventral shield or shell of
tortoises and turtles. See <er>Testudinata</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A trimming for the front of a woman's dress, made of
a different material, and narrowing from the shoulders to the
waist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-plasty</ent>⟦br⟧
